{.metadata}
``` toml
title = "djot-tools playground"
```

Open this directory as a workspace after building `target/debug/djot-ls`.
This small set of documents is meant for manual testing and demos.

# Start here

- [Language server playground](djot-ls.dj)
- [Metadata code-action scratchpad](metadata-scratch.dj)
- [Exporter playground](djot-export.dj)
- [Notes playground](djot-notes.dj)

# Suggested commands

``` sh
cargo build
djot-export examples/djot-export.dj | pandoc -f json -t markdown
djot-notes note --root examples --query 'title.matches("playground")'
djot-notes note --root examples --query '"index.dj" in directly_referenced_by'
djot-notes task --root examples --flat
djot-notes task --root examples --query 'created != null && done == null'
djot-notes task --root examples --query 'actionable'
djot-notes task --root examples --query 'blocked'
djot-notes task --root examples --query 'done != null'
djot-notes task --root examples --query 'canceled != null'
```

The three linked files intentionally cross-reference each other so
`djot-notes` reverse-reference queries have useful output.
